tyle=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text;height:40px;width:73.9844px;text-align:center;vertical-align:middle\">-</td>\n<td style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text;height:40px;width:658.484px\">-</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text;height:30px\">\n<td style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text;height:40px;width:42.5312px\">10th</td>\n<td style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text;height:40px;width:73.9844px;text-align:center;vertical-align:middle\">-</td>\n<td style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text;height:40px;width:658.484px\">@Item[yFkUlV5M7jpGMRZE]{Spell Synthesis}</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<h2 style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text;border-bottom:1px solid var(--color-underline-header);color:#191813\">Scholars of the Arcane &amp; the Divine</h2>\n<p>Blurring the line between divine and arcane, mystic theurges draw power from divine sources and musty tomes alike. While most spellcasters choose one path to magical power, mystic theurges walk two roads at once.</p>\n<p>Mystic theurges have unparalleled diversity of spells. In time, a mystic theurge can cast almost any spell. Mystic theurges are often obsessed with magical lore, traveling to the ends of the earth to learn some new arcane secret or divine insight.</p>\n<p>Mystic theurges tend to be fascinated with magic in whatever form it takes. They’re always on the hunt for powerful magic items and new arcane spells. Those mystic theurges who worship a deity use the power of their spellcasting to further their deity’s agenda.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"https://www.dandwiki.com/wiki/Mystic_Theurge_(5e_Class)","identifier":"MysticTheurge","levels":1,"hitDice":"d6","hitDiceUsed":0,"advancement":[{"_id":"95saabhljn7qbosv","type":"HitPoints","configuration":{},"value":{}},{"_id":"gm7u6vbcdmqi010k","type":"ItemGrant","configuration":{"items":["Item.w8lGQKqD4rA0CJGb","Item.Aa95oiRO99hPYcnd"],"optional":false},"value":{},"level":1,"title